subject: p18322589
Findings: Portable AP radiograph of the chest was reviewed in comparison to. Since the prior radiograph there was interval insertion of right internal jugular line with its tip terminating in the level of cavoatrial junction. There is no evidence of pneumothorax or apical hematoma. The ET tube tip is 43 cm above the carina. The replaced mitral valve and the pacemaker leads are in unchanged position. Overall there is no change in widespread parenchymal opacities, bibasal atelectasis and pleural effusion.
